text: Gao Han (; born 3 July 1971) is a Chinese former track and field sprinter who competed in the 100 metres. She holds a personal best of 11.26 seconds, set in 1992.Gao Han. All Athletics. Retrieved on 2016-07-30. Gao was the Chinese national champion in the event in 1992 and won a bronze medal at the 1993 East Asian Games behind Wang Huei-Chen and Xiao Yehua.East Asian Games. GBR Athletics. Retrieved on 2016-07-30.Chinese Championships. GBR Athletics. Retrieved on 2016-07-30. She represented China at the 1992 Summer Olympics, reaching the quarter-finals of the women's 100 m and running in the first round of the 4 × 100 metres relay with team mates Tian Yumei, Chen Zhaojing, and Xiao Yehua.Gao Han . Sports Reference. Retrieved on 2016-07-30. Relay gold came later that year for the quartet at the 1992 IAAF World Cup.IAAF Statistics Book Split 2010. IAAF.
